-- Merrion Names Conlon Investment Unit CEO as O’Dwyer Retires
-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 2013-04-08T15:32:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-08/merrion-names-conlon-investment-unit-ceo-as-o-dwyer-retires.html
Merrion Capital Group appointed
David Conlon as head of its investment management unit,
replacing Joe O’Dwyer, who is retiring on health grounds,
according to an internal e-mail.  John Conroy, chief executive of Dublin-based Merrion
Capital, confirmed the internal communication. He declined to
comment further.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Brennan in Dublin at 
